        "tier": "TOPIC",
        "title": "Bee Reactor Adapter Package",
        "createdAt": "2026-04-21T19:32:46.310Z",
        "description": "Structure of the bee-reactor-adaptor monorepo: two npm packages, the src/channel + swarm-client + chat + plugin layout, and operational requirements.",
        "orientation": "The bee-reactor-adaptor is the concrete code artifact that turns Path A into a real install. It's a pnpm monorepo with two published packages: the adapter itself and a Connect fork. Inside the adapter, src/channel/ holds the Swarm-sync code, src/swarm-client.ts wraps Bee APIs, and src/chat and src/plugin house the PSS chat runtime and plugin orchestration. This MOC collects the code-map notes, the required-environment notes, and the shared encryption/ACT dependencies that define how the package fits into a Connect install."
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:49.000Z"
    }
